Package model

Class Piste

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.Piste
  • public class Piste
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the "Track" class, it will be used to create our track, regroup all obstacles and opponents but also set the interaction with checkpoints.

    • Method Detail

      • createTrack

        public void createTrack()
        Creates a track with two initial points at the bottom of the screen, and adds more points generated with the addPoint() method Also creates the CheckPointList and gives it the value of the horizon

      • addPoint

        public void addPoint()
        Adds a new Point at the horizon height to each part of the track. The point added to the left track has a random x and the point added to the right track is on its right

      • speedUp

        public void speedUp()
        Increases the speed by 2 if the current speed is not higher than 35

      • speedDown

        public void speedDown()
        Decreases the speed by 1 if the current speed is not lower than 10

      • moveTrack

        public void moveTrack()
        Moves the track and everything on it from back to front. Used also to give a perception of perspective.

      • trackEffect

        public void trackEffect​(java.lang.String mvStat,
                        int coef)
        Moves the track depending on the movement of the Vehicle : Zooms in or out of the vehicle goes lower or higher and moves the track to the right (left) if the vehicle goes to the left (right)
        Parameters:
        mvStat - a String, the direction of the vehicle, that indicates which movement the track does
        coef - an integer that indicates how big the movement is

      • checkObst

        public boolean checkObst​(Vehicule V)

        Parameters:
        V - the vehicle
        Returns:
        true if the vehicle is hitting an obstacle, false otherwise
